{"name":"Sage","type":"class","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/class.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.fdY0nOUU5Vu2p5Ra"}},"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><em>Esoteric magic has reformed the entirety of your being, the border between your body, mind and soul having long since blurred, your magic having reshaped you and your connection to reality. You’re capable of powerful and unorthodox feats of magic, the power to reshape yourself and reality within your hands.</em></p>\n<p><strong>Key Ability: Intelligence</strong></p>\n<p>At 1st level, your class gives you an ability boost to Intelligence.</p>\n<p><strong>Hit Points: 8 plus your Constitution modifier</strong></p>\n<p>You increase your maximum number of HP by this number at 1st level and every level thereafter.</p>\n<h1>Roleplaying the Sage</h1>\n<h2>During Combat Encounters...</h2>\n<p>You call upon your esoteric magics, weaving cantrips and spells between your strikes.</p>\n<h2>During Social Encounters...</h2>\n<p>Your knowledge of the world allows you to adapt to society.</p>\n<h2>While Exploring...</h2>\n<p>You can use your magic to gain information preemptively, understanding the rules and informing yourself of what may be to come. </p>\n<h2>In Downtime...</h2>\n<p>You continue to study in an attempt to understand the world and all of its knowledge. You may even inspire others to do the same.</p>\n<h2>You Might...</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Constantly pursue knowledge to better yourself and those around you.</li>\n<li>Seek to understand anything and everything you come across if you don’t already.</li>\n<li>Rant about topics of interest even though those around you don’t understand any of it.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Others Probably...</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Awe at your knowledge, seeking advice from you and your vast mind.</li>\n<li>Wonder how your magic is able to easily alter your body in ways they can’t comprehend.</li>\n<li>Think of you as a madman, your sometimes niche knowledge seeming like trickery due to it not being common.</li>\n</ul>\n<h1>Initial Proficiencies</h1>\n<p>At 1st level, you gain the listed proficiency ranks in the following statistics. You are untrained in anything not listed unless you gain a better proficiency rank in some other way.</p>\n<h2>Perception</h2>\n<p>Expert in Perception</p>\n<h2>Saving Throws</h2>\n<p>Trained in Fortitude</p>\n<p>Trained in Reflex</p>\n<p>Trained in Will</p>\n<h2>Skills</h2>\n<p>Trained in Occultism</p>\n<p>Trained in a number of additional skills equal to 5 plus your Intelligence modifier</p>\n<h2>Attacks</h2>\n<p>Trained in sage weapons</p>\n<p>Trained in simple weapons</p>\n<p>Trained in unarmed attacks</p>\n<h2>Defenses</h2>\n<p>Untrained in all armor</p>\n<p>Trained in unarmored defense</p>\n<h2>Spells</h2>\n<p>Trained in occult spell attacks</p>\n<p>Trained in occult spell DCs</p>\n<h1>Class Features</h1>\n<p>You gain these features as a Sage. Abilities gained at higher levels list the levels at which you gain them next to the features' names.</p>\n<table class=\"pf2-table\" style=\"width:100%;height:614px\">\n<thead>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<th style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">Your Level</th>\n<th style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">Class Features</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">Ancestry and background, initial proficiencies, sagely spellcasting, spell repertoire, esoteric knowledge, accolade spells, molded protection, sagely weaponry</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:34px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:34px\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:34px\">Sage feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">3</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">2nd-level spells, general feat, signature spells, skill increase</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">4</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">Sage feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">5</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">3rd-level spells, ability boosts, ancestry feat, sage's focus, skill increase</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">6</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">Sage feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">7</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">4th-level spells, expert spellcaster, general feat, skill increase</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">8</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">Sage feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">9</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">5th-level spells, ancestry feat, great fortitude, resolve, skill increase</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">10</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">Ability boosts, Sage feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">11</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">6th-level spells, sage's defence, sage weapon expertise, general feat, skill increase</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">12</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">Sage feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">13</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">7th-level spells, ancestry feat, light armor expertise, skill increase, Sage's weapon specialization</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">14</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">Sage feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">15</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">8th-level spells, ability boosts, general feat, master spellcaster, skill increase</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">16</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">Sage feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">17</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">9th-level spells, ancestry feat, precognitive awareness, skill increase</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">18</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">Sage feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">19</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">Awakened sage, general feat, legendary spellcaster, skill increase</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<td style=\"width:8.9798%;height:29px\">20</td>\n<td style=\"width:90.9312%;height:29px\">Ability boosts, Sage feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>Ancestry and Background</h2>\n<p>In addition to the abilities provided by your class at 1st level, you have the benefits of your selected ancestry and background.</p>\n<h2>Initial Proficiencies</h2>\n<p>At 1st level, you gain a number of proficiencies that represent your basic training. These proficiencies are noted at the start of this class.</p>\n<h2>Sagely Spellcasting</h2>\n<p>You’ve become a being of pure magic and as such casting spells is second nature to you. You can cast occult spells using the Cast a Spell activity. You can substitute any material component with a somatic component, which can be a simple wave of your hand, eliminating the need for a material component pouch when casting spells. Also, you can substitute somatic components with verbal components.</p>\n<p>Each day, you can cast one 1st-level spell. You must know spells to cast them, and you learn them via the spell repertoire class feature. The number of spells you can cast each day is called your spell slots.</p>\n<p>As you increase in level as a sage, your number of spells per day increases, as does the higher level of spells you can cast, as shown on Table 2: Sage Spells per Day.</p>\n<p>Some of your spells require you to attempt a spell attack roll to see how effective they are, or have your enemies roll against your spell DC (typically by attempting a saving throw). Since your key ability is Intelligence, your spell attack rolls and spell DCs use your Intelligence modifier.</p>\n<h3><strong>Heightening Spells</strong></h3>\n<p>When you get spell slots of 2nd level and higher, you can fill those slots with stronger versions of lower-level spells. This increases the spell's level to match the spell slot. You must have a spell in your spell repertoire at the level you want to cast in order to heighten it to that level. Many spells have specific improvements when they are heightened to certain levels. The signature spells class feature lets you heighten certain spells freely.</p>\n<h3><strong>Cantrips</strong></h3>\n<p>Some of your spells are cantrips. A cantrip is a special type of spell that doesn't use spell slots. You can cast a cantrip at will, any number of times per day. A cantrip is automatically heightened to half your level rounded up -- this is usually equal to the highest level of bard spell slot you have. For example, as a 1st-level bard, your cantrips are 1st-level spells, and as a 5th-level bard, your cantrips are 3rd-level spells.</p>\n<table class=\"pf2-table\" style=\"width:100%\"><caption>Table 2: Sage Spells per Day</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width:13.1868%\">Your Level</th>\n<th style=\"width:11.8343%\">Cantrips</th>\n<th style=\"width:7.18512%\">1st</th>\n<th style=\"width:7.69231%\">2nd</th>\n<th style=\"width:7.43872%\">3rd</th>\n<th style=\"width:7.35418%\">4th</th>\n<th style=\"width:7.35418%\">5th</th>\n<th style=\"width:7.35418%\">6th</th>\n<th style=\"width:7.35418%\">7th</th>\n<th style=\"width:7.35418%\">8th</th